text: Tahmeed Rahman (born 26 September 1998) is an Indian cricketer. He made his List A debut for Nagaland in the 2018–19 Vijay Hazare Trophy on 19 September 2018. He made his first-class debut for Nagaland in the 2018–19 Ranji Trophy on 1 November 2018. In round five of the 2018–19 Ranji Trophy, in the match against Manipur, Rahman took a hat-trick. He made his Twenty20 debut for Nagaland in the 2018–19 Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy on 21 February 2019. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:Indian cricketers Category:Nagaland cricketers Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
